            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="WORKS"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Bath and North East Somerset Council Highways Maintenance and Improvement Contract.</P>
               <P>The scope of the service includes:</P>
               <P>— Carriageway resurfacing and surface treatments.</P>
               <P>— Improvement schemes and minor construction works.</P>
               <P>— Cyclic maintenance (Grass cutting, gulley cleansing, grip cutting).</P>
               <P>— Minor structural maintenance.</P>
               <P>— Highways inspector gangs.</P>
               <P>— Winter gritting and fleet management.</P>
               <P>— Road markings and studs.</P>
               <P>— Fencing and barriers.</P>
               <P>— Emergency response.</P>
               <P>— Event traffic management.</P>
               <P>— Off-highway works.</P>
               <P>Litter picking on highway verge is optional.</P>
               <P>The scope will NOT include:</P>
               <P>— Traffic signals.</P>
               <P>— Street lighting.</P>
               <P>— Highways structures (major works).</P>
               <P>— Safety and network inspections.</P>
               <P>— Core design work for resurfacing or improvement schemes.</P>
               <P>— Winter decision making.</P>
               <P>— Purchase of salt.</P>
               <P>— Customer contact centre and community interface.</P>
               <P>The total value of the initial 7 year term is approximately 49 000 000 GBP. If extended to the full 10 years then the contract value would be approximately 70 000 000 GBP.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
